  description: "<p>COMPANY OVERVIEW</p> <p>Lodestone is looking for self-motivated engineers with software engineering and machine learning experience to join our team. As a Software Engineer, you will play a key role working with our client's Product, Engineering, Analytics, and Operations teams to build key data pipelines and tools to facilitate and enable teams to effectively perform data analysis and run experimentation. You will be supporting machine learning, statistical experimentation, and data collection.</p> <p>WHO YOU ARE</p> <p>You enjoy working with a small team in a growing company that has direct client impact. You have experience with independently leading a technical project that is client focused. You enjoy solving technical problems and interacting with the core platform software team and product teams. This is a hybrid software engineering role, so you have a solid SWE background but are familiar with data science, ML, and statistics. This role is responsible for handling technical support &amp; statistical analysis in our software operations support team.</p> <p>RESPONSIBILITIES</p> <p>Gather and implement technical requirements, and work closely with product and cross-functional teams to support key product initiatives</p> <p>Pre-process large amounts of data and feature engineering</p> <p>Conduct statistical modeling for analyses and report metrics and findings</p> <p>Enhance overall system reliability, performance, efficiency, and scalability of new platform features</p> <p>Configure backend and frontend software components, and tools</p> <p>MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS</p> <p>Ability to execute independently in an ambiguous environment</p> <p>Ability to manage time / scope effectively and prioritize issues while maintaining the level of quality and efficiency</p> <p>3+ years programming experience in C, C++, Java, PHP, or Python</p> <p>3+ years experience in writing SQL statements</p> <p>2+ years experience with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript Frameworks such as REACT or similar</p> <p>2+ years experience with statistical testing and machine learning</p> <p>2+ years experience with dashboarding and data visualization</p> <p>3+ years industry experience in the technology sector</p> <p>Thorough understanding of XML, JSON, and data structure fundamentals</p> <p>Ability to independently and creatively solve problems</p> <p>PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS</p> <ul> <li> <p>Undergraduate or masters degree in computer science, statistics or related technical field, or equivalent related experience</p> </li> <li> <p>5+ years experience software development or data science experience</p> </li> </ul> ",
